<br>
Welcome to bbarden network's newest forum. The aim of this forum is self explanatory: It is intended for serious debates. Although very rewarding, problems can and do often occur from mis-use in this forum, which is why a special set of rules and guidelines have been drawn up. Please read them carefully.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Rules<br>
1. No Spamming<br>
2. No Flaming<br>
3. Any part of these discussions may be re-produced by the forum owners, without prior consent, for both internal and external uses.<br>
</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Debates Dos and Don'ts<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Do</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Read every article and reply carefully and thoughtfully before replying.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Do</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Try to understand what the other users are trying to say.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Do</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Take a little time to think before replying.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Do</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Bring up points that need answering or need further clarification.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Do</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Use the Quote EZtag to make your replies easier to understand.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Do</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Try to be to the point.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Do</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Answer questions posed.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Do</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Back down over arguments if they don't look like being solved.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Don't</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Prejudge an article by title or opening paragraph.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Don't </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Skim through replies and judge.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Don't </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Generalise user groups.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Don't</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Insult people directly.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Don't</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Over quote to devalue someone's argument.<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Don't </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> linger on the same argument for too long.<br>
<br>
Finally - Please remember there is always more then one side to an argument, and that people like yourself will think that their reasons are as correct and obviously true as your own.<br>
<br>
